Philippe Coutinho wants to join Chelsea from Barcelona, according to Duncan Castles. Coutinho looks set to leave Barcelona this summer after a difficult 18 months and the club are ready to sell. “The briefing I had last week was that Coutinho’s preference would be to go to Chelsea rather than Paris St-Germain,” Castles said on the Transfer Window podcast. “But of course, dependent on the transfer-window ban being lifted, which it looks almost certain not to happen.” Barcelona eye Angel Di Maria after Coutinho''s frustration Liverpool demand €150m from Barcelona for Coutinho Barcelona hopeful over Coutinho Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin